kind of your job,

00:36:24.763 --> 00:36:26.430
it's obviously a very
high-pressure job,

00:36:26.430 --> 00:36:27.740
and there's a lot of--

00:36:27.740 --> 00:36:30.180
the energy must be
really crazy, probably

00:36:30.180 --> 00:36:31.608
really takes a lot out of you.

00:36:31.608 --> 00:36:33.900
So I'm wondering how do you
actually balance your life?

00:36:33.900 --> 00:36:35.970
You talked a little bit about
it between your family life

00:36:35.970 --> 00:36:37.800
and personal, but what
do you do personally

00:36:37.800 --> 00:36:40.260
to kind of take the edge off
when things get-- when they

00:36:40.260 --> 00:36:42.093
escalate, when you're
on tour, for whatever,

00:36:42.093 --> 00:36:44.898
eight weeks,
non-stop, et cetera.

00:36:44.898 --> 00:36:46.190
KELLY JONES: Not enough really.

00:36:46.190 --> 00:36:49.890
I'm pretty crap at giving
myself any time, I have to say.

00:36:49.890 --> 00:36:54.760
I kind of get into a bit of
a treadmill, of when I start,

00:36:54.760 --> 00:36:57.330
I'll do the work, and
I'll do the shows,

00:36:57.330 --> 00:36:59.195
and I kind of get
engrossed in it.

00:36:59.195 --> 00:37:00.570
And when I'm with
the family, I'm

00:37:00.570 --> 00:37:02.050
very much engrossed in that.

00:37:02.050 --> 00:37:06.540
And the only thing I kind of do
outside of that really is I'll

00:37:06.540 --> 00:37:12.238
go for a run or something
like that, or watch films,

00:37:12.238 --> 00:37:13.030
